org.wonderly.jini2.browse
Class JiniDeskTop

java.lang.Object
  org.wonderly.jini2.NameableObjectImpl
      org.wonderly.jini2.ConfigurableJiniApplication
          org.wonderly.jini2.browse.JiniDeskTop
All Implemented Interfaces:
NameableObject, ServiceLookupHandler
public class JiniDeskTop
extends ConfigurableJiniApplication
implements ServiceLookupHandler

This is an application meant to be given to users in an environment where serviceUI is the means of getting to applications. The users can startup this application, and it will find serviceUI accesible services, and then let the user organize a desktop and open and close serviceUI implementations.

Author:
Gregg Wonderly - gregg.wonderly@pobox.com

addRole

protected void addRole(String name,
                       ServiceRegistrar reg,
                       ServiceItem svcItem,
                       UIDescriptor uid,
                       String icon,
                       String group,
                       boolean trans,
                       List<HelpEntry> helps)
Create a new desktop Item for the named service using the indicated UIDescriptor for the serviceUI.

Parameters:
name - the name for the service typically from a Name Entry.
reg - the registrar we learned about it from
svcItem - the associated ServiceItem
uid - the UIDescriptor for the serviceUI
icon - the icon to use
group - the group this role should be associated with
trans - is this a transient or persistent registration?
See Also:
DesktopGroup, DesktopIcon
